## 6. CONSTRAINTS & VALIDATION RULES

### 6.1 Monetary Values
- **ALL money is integer** (BigInteger) — no decimals, no floats
- Currency: IQD (Iraqi Dinar)
- Values represent the smallest unit (fils), though typically treated as whole dinars

### 6.2 Stock Management
- Products have `stock_quantity` (aggregate of variants)
- Variants have individual `stock_quantity`
- On sale: deduct from variant first, then recalculate product aggregate
- Stock cannot go negative (CHECK constraint)

### 6.3 Soft Delete Pattern
- All DATA tables have `is_deleted` + `deleted_at`
- Partial unique indexes exclude deleted rows
- No hard deletes in application code

### 6.4 Idempotency
- `SaleCreate` requires `idempotency_key` (8-80 chars)
- `PaymentCreate` requires `idempotency_key`
- Duplicate keys within tenant return existing record with `replayed: true`

### 6.5 Sale Lifecycle
```
draft/active → active → completed
                    ↘ cancelled
```
- Cash sales auto-complete
- Installment sales complete when all installments fully paid

### 6.6 Installment Plan Lifecycle
```
active → completed (all paid)
     → defaulted (manual/admin)
     → cancelled (sale cancelled)
     → superseded (rescheduled)
```

